I wanted to ask you since I don't know a lot of people working in the same industry.  Leah messaged me about a year ago and then blocked me right after, but she said she "Left the software industry" and I couldn't understand why?  What am I missing?  Other people save up their big payouts and go on vacations.  Is women in tech really as bad as the media says?  Does technology move so quickly that by the time it's fun it is already obsolete?  Am I too vested in the business outcome and completely missing out on a life passing me by?  A year ago when I got laid off, I wanted to quit and find something else to do, like growing flowers.  Where are you at with this?
Sexism is still rather rampant in this industry, I’ve seen it first hand and heard too many stories.
